President Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of West Virginia due to severe storms and flooding that occurred from February 27 to March 4, 2021. This declaration allows for Federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Cabell, Kanawha, Mingo, and Wayne are eligible for federal funding, which can include grants for temporary housing, home repairs, low-cost loans for property losses, and other recovery programs. Federal funding is also available for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures statewide. Deanne Criswell, the Administrator of FEMA, has named Jeffrey L. Jones as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by calling the provided toll-free telephone numbers. Further information can be obtained by contacting the FEMA News Desk.